did.abstract: Contains records related to student admissions, academic progress, grades, graduation, scholarships, fellowships, special academic programs, graduate students, and academic withdrawals.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: Officially established in 1962 when the Dean of the College position was divided into the Dean of the Faculty and the Dean of Studies, the Dean of Studies office executes educational policies as they relate to students and enforces faculty legislation regarding requirements for degrees.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: The collection contains records related to student admissions, academic progress, grades, graduation, scholarships, fellowships, special academic programs, graduate students, and academic withdrawals.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into two series: Series I. Student Records, 1867-2016; and Series II. Administrative Records, undated.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Records of the Dean of Studies are restricted to College use only.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Permission to quote (publish) from unpublished or previously published material must be obtained as described in the regulations of the Vassar College Archives and Special Collections Library .
